Gas transfer model issue resolved

Summary:

The issue didt have anything to do with the gas exchange models after all, but rather poor coding that failed to synchronize gas flux with depth integrated DO observations. Daily NEP and ER estimates based on the seven gas exchange models now accord much better.

NEP:

Daily NEP estimates for Crystal Lake based on seven gas flux models. The time series line is the mean of NEP from other models and the shaded bounds are the maximum and minimum of the NEP estimates at each daily time step.

ER:

Daily ER values from NEP estimates. Figure layout is same as NEP estimates.
